One Sabbath Jesus was going through the grainfields, and his disciples began to pick some heads of grain as they made their way.
The Pharisees said to Jesus, "Look! It is against the law to do this on the Sabbath. Why are your disciples doing it?"
He replied, "Have you never read what David did? He and his men were hungry. They needed food.
It was at the time when Abiathar was high priest that David entered the house of God and ate the consecrated bread. Only the priests were allowed to eat it, but David also gave some to his men.
Then Jesus said to them, "The Sabbath was made for man, not man for the Sabbath."
Therefore the Son of Man is also Lord of the Sabbath.
Healing on Saturday
And Jesus went again into the synagogue; and there was a man there whose hand was withered.
Some Pharisees were trying to find fault with Jesus. They were watching him closely. They wanted to see whether he would heal the man on the Sabbath.
Jesus spoke to the man who had a withered and twisted hand. He said to him, "Stand up before everyone."
And after that, Jesus asked them, "What does the law say we should do on the Sabbath? Should we do good or evil? Should we save lives or kill?" But no one answered.
Jesus looked at them with anger. He was deeply disturbed because their hearts were hard. Then he said to the man, "Stretch out your hand." He stretched it out, and his hand was restored, as sound as the other.
Then the Pharisees went out and began to plot with the Herodians against Jesus, how they might destroy Him. The multitudes followed Jesus.
Jesus walked with his disciples to the Sea of Galilee, and great crowds from Galilee followed them.
When the people heard all that Jesus was doing, many came to him. They came from Judea, Jerusalem, Idumea, beyond the Jordan, and the region around Tyre and Sidon.
Because of the crowd, Jesus asked his disciples to prepare a small boat for him. This way, he could avoid being pressed by the people.
Jesus had healed many people. So the sick were jostling to touch him.
And the people who had evil spirits in them fell down before him. And the cries of the spirits: "This is the Son of God!"
